==Spanish==
===Verb===
'''diga''', also '''[[digame]]'''

Imperative singular formal of ''[[dir]]'', '''say''' or '''tell'''

# [[say]], [[talk]], [[speak]]
# way to say [[Hello]] on the [[telephone]] in some countries of Latin America.
#: "Diga." (Talk!); "Digame." ("Talk to me.", "Say something to me.")

====Synonyms====
*[[bueno]] (2)

====Etymology====
From Latin ''[[dicat]]'', third person singular present subjunctive active of ''[[dicere]]'', '''say''' or '''tell'''.  The subjunctive (''dicat'', '''may he say''') became the Spanish polite imperative (''diga'', ''diga usted'', '''may your mercy say''').